{
  "texts": [
    "This is vital for understanding the attribution of responsibility (Jelodar et al. 2019), and identifying the recurrent issues and themes within the overall discourse, the interests of various actors, and the major causes contributing to problematic issues (Benites-Lazaro et al. 2018b).",
    "Topic modeling can also be applied to track temporal changes in the prevalence of topics within climate change discourse (Blei and Lafferty 2006).",
    "Such approaches can reveal how discussion of the issues has evolved over time to reveal major cultural shifts, and hence provide a deeper, diachronic understanding of the problem space (Hoffman 2015).",
    "Although topic modelling is a commonly used and highly insightful technique, it is predicated on the analysis of the text at the document level.",
    "To identify the specific roles played by individual actors within the text, it is necessary first to reliably extract them and second to identify their semantic role."
  ]
}